Name: Beaphar Gentle Leader for Medium & Large Dogs
Description:
Beaphar Gentle Leader for Medium & Large DogsGentle Leader simply &  easily converts into a regular collar for greater flexibility.Gentle Leader was designed by a foremost veterinary surgeon and a past President of the National Association of Dog Trainers in the USA. The Gentle Leader enables owners to prevent their dog or puppy from pulling on the lead and makes training in basic obedience (sit, stay, down, come etc) really quick and easy because of its three-fold natural effect on the way dogs think, relax and behave.Why Choose Gentle Leader?

Dogs of all sizes pull on standard collars and harnesses due to a natural instinct to pull against pressure. The Gentle Leader & unique Triple Action, Patented Design counters that instinct in 3 ways:
Gentle pressure is transferred to the back of the neck, naturally stimulating a relaxation response (the same as when a mother carries a puppy by the scruff of it neck).
Gentle pressure around the muzzle of the nose loop naturally gives a relaxation response.
It works like a halter on a horse where the nose goes the body will follow.

Instructions
1. Attach your dog’s normal lead to the control ring2. Release the buckle on the neck strap and hold it at each end3. Fit the neck strap around your dog’s neck so that it is touching the base of your dog’s skull at the back and snug above their Adam’s apple at the front.4. You should be able to squeeze one finger underneath the neck strap. This will appear to fit more snugly than a normal collar, but your dog will still be comfortable5. Release the buckle and remove the neck strap from your dog.6. Open the adjustable sliding clamp and slide this down towards the control ring where the lead is attached.7. Pull the nose loop up through the centre double D-ring, which is located at the central part of the ‘T’ shape.8. Holding the neck strap in your hands, slide the nose loop which you have just created over your dog’s nose. Then, connect both ends of the neck strap around your dog’s neck.9. Move the adjustable sliding clamp up so it sits just below your dog’s jaw.10. The nose loop should now sit in front of your dog’s eyes but behind the corners of their mouth, and be loose enough to be pulled forward to the start of the fleshy part of their nose.11. Make a final adjustment to the nose loop and then close the adjustable sliding clamp.12. Once fitted in this way, it should not be necessary to re-open the adjustable sliding clamp, unless your dog is still growing.
